name: Eilenberg–MacLane space
summary:
In mathematics, specifically algebraic topology, an Eilenberg–MacLane space is a topological space with a single nontrivial homotopy group.
Let G be a group and n a positive integer. A connected topological space X is called an Eilenberg–MacLane space of type
